        "x": 0,
        "y": 28
      },
      "id": 9,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Mean Reversion Strategy Analysis for HYPE\n\n**Hypothesis**: After large taker orders (top 5% by size), the price tends to revert partially.\n\n**How it works**:\n- **Large BUY taker** = aggressive buyer hits asks, pushes price UP temporarily\n  - If price reverts (goes back DOWN), the fade would profit\n- **Large SELL taker** = aggressive seller hits bids, pushes price DOWN temporarily  \n  - If price reverts (goes back UP), the fade would profit\n\n**Key Metrics**:\n- **Reversion Rate**: % of large orders where price moved in favorable direction within 5 minutes\n- **Expected Value (EV)**: Average profit per trade if you faded every large order\n- **Positive EV** = profitable strategy over time",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Strategy Summary",
      "type": "text"
    }
